Class.Name: NSString
Class.Description: A static, plain-text Unicode string object.

InstanceMethods.Name: init
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an initialized NSString object that contains no characters.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithBytes:length:encoding:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an initialized NSString object containing a given number of bytes from a given buffer of bytes interpreted in a given encoding.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithBytesNoCopy:length:encoding:freeWhenDone:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an initialized NSString object that contains a given number of bytes from a given buffer of bytes interpreted in a given encoding, and optionally frees the buffer.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithCharacters:length:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an initialized NSString object that contains a given number of characters from a given C array of UTF-16 code units.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithCharactersNoCopy:length:freeWhenDone:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an initialized NSString object that contains a given number of characters from a given C array of UTF-16 code units.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithString:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an NSString object initialized by copying the characters from another given string.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithCString:encoding:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an NSString object initialized using the characters in a given C array, interpreted according to a given encoding.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithUTF8String:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an NSString object initialized by copying the characters from a given C array of UTF8-encoded bytes.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithFormat:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an NSString object initialized by using a given format string as a template into which the remaining argument values are substituted.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithFormat:arguments:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an NSString object initialized by using a given format string as a template into which the remaining argument values are substituted without any localization.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithFormat:locale:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an NSString object initialized by using a given format string as a template into which the remaining argument values are substituted according to given locale.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithFormat:locale:arguments:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an NSString object initialized by using a given format string as a template into which the remaining argument values are substituted according to given locale information. This method is meant to be called from within a variadic function, where the argument list will be available.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithData:encoding:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an NSString object initialized by converting given data into UTF-16 code units using a given encoding.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithContentsOfFile:encoding:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an NSString object initialized by reading data from the file at a given path using a given encoding.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithContentsOfFile:usedEncoding:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an NSString object initialized by reading data from the file at a given path and returns by reference the encoding used to interpret the characters.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithContentsOfURL:encoding:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an NSString object initialized by reading data from a given URL interpreted using a given encoding.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithContentsOfURL:usedEncoding:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an NSString object initialized by reading data from a given URL and returns by reference the encoding used to interpret the data.

InstanceMethods.Name: lengthOfBytesUsingEncoding:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the number of bytes required to store the receiver in a given encoding.

InstanceMethods.Name: maximumLengthOfBytesUsingEncoding:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the maximum number of bytes needed to store the receiver in a given encoding.

InstanceMethods.Name: characterAtIndex:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the character at a given UTF-16 code unit index.

InstanceMethods.Name: getCharacters:range:
InstanceMethods.Description: Copies characters from a given range in the receiver into a given buffer.

InstanceMethods.Name: getBytes:maxLength:usedLength:encoding:options:range:remainingRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Gets a given range of characters as bytes in a specified encoding.

InstanceMethods.Name: cStringUsingEncoding:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a representation of the string as a C string using a given encoding.

InstanceMethods.Name: getCString:maxLength:encoding:
InstanceMethods.Description: Converts the string to a given encoding and stores it in a buffer.

InstanceMethods.Name: caseInsensitiveCompare:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the result of invoking compare:options: with NSCaseInsensitiveSearch as the only option.

InstanceMethods.Name: localizedCaseInsensitiveCompare:
InstanceMethods.Description: Compares the string with a given string using a case-insensitive, localized, comparison.

InstanceMethods.Name: compare:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the result of invoking compare:options:range: with no options and the receiverâ€™s full extent as the range.

InstanceMethods.Name: localizedCompare:
InstanceMethods.Description: Compares the string and a given string using a localized comparison.

InstanceMethods.Name: compare:options:
InstanceMethods.Description: Compares the string with the specified string using the given options.

InstanceMethods.Name: compare:options:range:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the result of invoking compare:options:range:locale: with a nil locale.

InstanceMethods.Name: compare:options:range:locale:
InstanceMethods.Description: Compares the string using the specified options and returns the lexical ordering for the range.

InstanceMethods.Name: localizedStandardCompare:
InstanceMethods.Description: Compares strings as sorted by the Finder.

InstanceMethods.Name: hasPrefix:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether a given string matches the beginning characters of the receiver.

InstanceMethods.Name: hasSuffix:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether a given string matches the ending characters of the receiver.

InstanceMethods.Name: isEqualToString:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether a given string is equal to the receiver using a literal Unicode-based comparison.

InstanceMethods.Name: stringByAppendingFormat:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a string made by appending to the receiver a string constructed from a given format string and the following arguments.

InstanceMethods.Name: stringByAppendingString:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new string made by appending a given string to the receiver.

InstanceMethods.Name: stringByPaddingToLength:withString:startingAtIndex:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new string formed from the receiver by either removing characters from the end, or by appending as many occurrences as necessary of a given pad string.

InstanceMethods.Name: lowercaseStringWithLocale:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a version of the string with all letters converted to lowercase, taking into account the specified locale.

InstanceMethods.Name: uppercaseStringWithLocale:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a version of the string with all letters converted to uppercase, taking into account the specified locale.

InstanceMethods.Name: capitalizedStringWithLocale:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a capitalized representation of the receiver using the specified locale.

InstanceMethods.Name: componentsSeparatedByString:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an array containing substrings from the receiver that have been divided by a given separator.

InstanceMethods.Name: componentsSeparatedByCharactersInSet:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an array containing substrings from the receiver that have been divided by characters in a given set.

InstanceMethods.Name: stringByTrimmingCharactersInSet:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new string made by removing from both ends of the receiver characters contained in a given character set.

InstanceMethods.Name: substringFromIndex:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new string containing the characters of the receiver from the one at a given index to the end.

InstanceMethods.Name: substringWithRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a string object containing the characters of the receiver that lie within a given range.

InstanceMethods.Name: substringToIndex:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new string containing the characters of the receiver up to, but not including, the one at a given index.

InstanceMethods.Name: stringByFoldingWithOptions:locale:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates a string suitable for comparison by removing the specified character distinctions from a string.

InstanceMethods.Name: stringByApplyingTransform:reverse:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new string by applying a specified transform to the string.

InstanceMethods.Name: containsString:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the string contains a given string by performing a case-sensitive, locale-unaware search.

InstanceMethods.Name: localizedCaseInsensitiveContainsString:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the string contains a given string by performing a case-insensitive, locale-aware search.

InstanceMethods.Name: localizedStandardContainsString:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the string contains a given string by performing a case and diacritic insensitive, locale-aware search.

InstanceMethods.Name: rangeOfCharacterFromSet:
InstanceMethods.Description: Finds and returns the range in the string of the first character from a given character set.

InstanceMethods.Name: rangeOfCharacterFromSet:options:
InstanceMethods.Description: Finds and returns the range in the string of the first character, using given options, from a given character set.

InstanceMethods.Name: rangeOfCharacterFromSet:options:range:
InstanceMethods.Description: Finds and returns the range in the string of the first character from a given character set found in a given range with given options.

InstanceMethods.Name: rangeOfString:
InstanceMethods.Description: Finds and returns the range of the first occurrence of a given string within the string.

InstanceMethods.Name: rangeOfString:options:
InstanceMethods.Description: Finds and returns the range of the first occurrence of a given string within the string, subject to given options.

InstanceMethods.Name: rangeOfString:options:range:
InstanceMethods.Description: Finds and returns the range of the first occurrence of a given string, within the given range of the string, subject to given options.

InstanceMethods.Name: rangeOfString:options:range:locale:
InstanceMethods.Description: Finds and returns the range of the first occurrence of a given string within a given range of the string, subject to given options, using the specified locale, if any.

InstanceMethods.Name: localizedStandardRangeOfString:
InstanceMethods.Description: Finds and returns the range of the first occurrence of a given string within the string by performing a case and diacritic insensitive, locale-aware search.

InstanceMethods.Name: enumerateLinesUsingBlock:
InstanceMethods.Description: Enumerates all the lines in the string.

InstanceMethods.Name: enumerateSubstringsInRange:options:usingBlock:
InstanceMethods.Description: Enumerates the substrings of the specified type in the specified range of the string.

InstanceMethods.Name: stringByReplacingOccurrencesOfString:withString:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new string in which all occurrences of a target string in the receiver are replaced by another given string.

InstanceMethods.Name: stringByReplacingOccurrencesOfString:withString:options:range:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new string in which all occurrences of a target string in a specified range of the receiver are replaced by another given string.

InstanceMethods.Name: stringByReplacingCharactersInRange:withString:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new string in which the characters in a specified range of the receiver are replaced by a given string.

InstanceMethods.Name: commonPrefixWithString:options:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a string containing characters the receiver and a given string have in common, starting from the beginning of each up to the first characters that arenâ€™t equivalent.

InstanceMethods.Name: enumerateLinguisticTagsInRange:scheme:options:orthography:usingBlock:
InstanceMethods.Description: Performs linguistic analysis on the specified string by enumerating the specific range of the string, providing the Block with the located tags.
InstanceMethods.Declaration:
- (void)enumerateLinguisticTagsInRange:(NSRange)range 
                                scheme:(NSLinguisticTagScheme)scheme 
                               options:(NSLinguisticTaggerOptions)options 
                           orthography:(NSOrthography *)orthography 
                            usingBlock:(void (^)(NSLinguisticTag tag, NSRange tokenRange, NSRange sentenceRange, BOOL *stop))block;

InstanceMethods.Name: linguisticTagsInRange:scheme:options:orthography:tokenRanges:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an array of linguistic tags for the specified range and requested tags within the receiving string.

InstanceMethods.Name: getLineStart:end:contentsEnd:forRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns by reference the beginning of the first line and the end of the last line touched by the given range.

InstanceMethods.Name: lineRangeForRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the range of characters representing the line or lines containing a given range.

InstanceMethods.Name: getParagraphStart:end:contentsEnd:forRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns by reference the beginning of the first paragraph and the end of the last paragraph touched by the given range.

InstanceMethods.Name: paragraphRangeForRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the range of characters representing the paragraph or paragraphs containing a given range.

InstanceMethods.Name: rangeOfComposedCharacterSequenceAtIndex:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the range in the receiver of the composed character sequence located at a given index.

InstanceMethods.Name: rangeOfComposedCharacterSequencesForRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the range in the string of the composed character sequences for a given range.

InstanceMethods.Name: writeToFile:atomically:encoding:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Writes the contents of the receiver to a file at a given path using a given encoding.

InstanceMethods.Name: writeToURL:atomically:encoding:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Writes the contents of the receiver to the URL specified by url using the specified encoding.

InstanceMethods.Name: propertyList
InstanceMethods.Description: Parses the receiver as a text representation of a property list, returning an NSString, NSData, NSArray, or NSDictionary object, according to the topmost element.

InstanceMethods.Name: propertyListFromStringsFileFormat
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a dictionary object initialized with the keys and values found in the receiver.

InstanceMethods.Name: drawAtPoint:withAttributes:
InstanceMethods.Description: Draws the receiver with the font and other display characteristics of the given attributes, at the specified point in the current graphics context.

InstanceMethods.Name: drawInRect:withAttributes:
InstanceMethods.Description: Draws the attributed string inside the specified bounding rectangle.

InstanceMethods.Name: drawWithRect:options:attributes:context:
InstanceMethods.Description: Draws the attributed string in the specified bounding rectangle using the provided options.

InstanceMethods.Name: boundingRectWithSize:options:attributes:context:
InstanceMethods.Description: Calculates and returns the bounding rect for the receiver drawn using the given options and display characteristics, within the specified rectangle in the current graphics context.

InstanceMethods.Name: sizeWithAttributes:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the bounding box size the receiver occupies when drawn with the given attributes.

InstanceMethods.Name: variantFittingPresentationWidth:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a string variation suitable for the specified presentation width.

InstanceMethods.Name: canBeConvertedToEncoding:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether the receiver can be converted to a given encoding without loss of information.

InstanceMethods.Name: dataUsingEncoding:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an NSData object containing a representation of the receiver encoded using a given encoding.

InstanceMethods.Name: dataUsingEncoding:allowLossyConversion:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an NSData object containing a representation of the receiver encoded using a given encoding.

InstanceMethods.Name: completePathIntoString:caseSensitive:matchesIntoArray:filterTypes:
InstanceMethods.Description: Interprets the receiver as a path in the file system and attempts to perform filename completion, returning a numeric value that indicates whether a match was possible, and by reference the longest path that matches the receiver.

InstanceMethods.Name: getFileSystemRepresentation:maxLength:
InstanceMethods.Description: Interprets the receiver as a system-independent path and fills a buffer with a C-string in a format and encoding suitable for use with file-system calls.

InstanceMethods.Name: stringByAppendingPathComponent:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new string made by appending to the receiver a given string.

InstanceMethods.Name: stringByAppendingPathExtension:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new string made by appending to the receiver an extension separator followed by a given extension.

InstanceMethods.Name: stringsByAppendingPaths:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an array of strings made by separately appending to the receiver each string in a given array.

InstanceMethods.Name: stringByAddingPercentEncodingWithAllowedCharacters:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new string made from the receiver by replacing all characters not in the specified set with percent-encoded characters.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithCString:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes the receiver, a newly allocated NSString object, by converting the data in a given C-string from the default C-string encoding into the Unicode character encoding.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithCString:length:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes the receiver, a newly allocated NSString object, by converting the data in a given C-string from the default C-string encoding into the Unicode character encoding.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithCStringNoCopy:length:freeWhenDone:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes the receiver, a newly allocated NSString object, by converting the data in a given C-string from the default C-string encoding into the Unicode character encoding.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithContentsOfFile:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes the receiver, a newly allocated NSString object, by reading data from the file named by path.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithContentsOfURL:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes the receiver, a newly allocated NSString object, by reading data from the location named by a given URL.

InstanceMethods.Name: writeToFile:atomically:
InstanceMethods.Description: Writes the contents of the receiver to the file specified by a given path.

InstanceMethods.Name: writeToURL:atomically:
InstanceMethods.Description: Writes the contents of the receiver to the location specified by a given URL.

InstanceMethods.Name: getCharacters:
InstanceMethods.Description: Copies all characters from the receiver into a given buffer.

InstanceMethods.Name: cString
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a representation of the receiver as a C string in the default C-string encoding.

InstanceMethods.Name: lossyCString
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a representation of the receiver as a C string in the default C-string encoding, possibly losing information in converting to that encoding.

InstanceMethods.Name: cStringLength
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the length in char-sized units of the receiverâ€™s C-string representation in the default C-string encoding.

InstanceMethods.Name: getCString:
InstanceMethods.Description: Invokes getCString:maxLength:range:remainingRange: with NSMaximumStringLength as the maximum length, the receiverâ€™s entire extent as the range, and NULL for the remaining range.

InstanceMethods.Name: getCString:maxLength:
InstanceMethods.Description: Invokes getCString:maxLength:range:remainingRange: with maxLength as the maximum length in char-sized units, the receiverâ€™s entire extent as the range, and NULL for the remaining range.

InstanceMethods.Name: getCString:maxLength:range:remainingRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Converts the receiverâ€™s content to the default C-string encoding and stores them in a given buffer.

InstanceMethods.Name: stringByAddingPercentEscapesUsingEncoding:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a representation of the receiver using a given encoding to determine the percent escapes necessary to convert the receiver into a legal URL string.

InstanceMethods.Name: stringByReplacingPercentEscapesUsingEncoding:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new string made by replacing in the receiver all percent escapes with the matching characters as determined by a given encoding.

InstanceMethods.Name: sizeWithFont:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the size of the string if it were to be rendered with the specified font on a single line.

InstanceMethods.Name: sizeWithFont:forWidth:lineBreakMode:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the size of the string if it were to be rendered with the specified font and line attributes on a single line.

InstanceMethods.Name: sizeWithFont:minFontSize:actualFontSize:forWidth:lineBreakMode:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the size of the string if it were rendered with the specified constraints, including a variable font size, on a single line.

InstanceMethods.Name: sizeWithFont:constrainedToSize:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the size of the string if it were rendered and constrained to the specified size.

InstanceMethods.Name: sizeWithFont:constrainedToSize:lineBreakMode:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the size of the string if it were rendered with the specified constraints.

InstanceMethods.Name: drawAtPoint:withFont:
InstanceMethods.Description: Draws the string in a single line at the specified point in the current graphics context using the specified font.

InstanceMethods.Name: drawAtPoint:forWidth:withFont:lineBreakMode:
InstanceMethods.Description: Draws the string in a single line at the specified point in the current graphics context using the specified font and attributes.

InstanceMethods.Name: drawAtPoint:forWidth:withFont:fontSize:lineBreakMode:baselineAdjustment:
InstanceMethods.Description: Draws the string in a single line at the specified point in the current graphics context using the specified font and attributes.

InstanceMethods.Name: drawAtPoint:forWidth:withFont:minFontSize:actualFontSize:lineBreakMode:baselineAdjustment:
InstanceMethods.Description: Draws the string in a single line with the specified font and attributes, adjusting the font attributes as needed to render as much of the text as possible.

InstanceMethods.Name: drawInRect:withFont:
InstanceMethods.Description: Draws the string in the current graphics context using the specified bounding rectangle and font.

InstanceMethods.Name: drawInRect:withFont:lineBreakMode:
InstanceMethods.Description: Draws the string in the current graphics context using the specified bounding rectangle, font, and attributes.

InstanceMethods.Name: drawInRect:withFont:lineBreakMode:alignment:
InstanceMethods.Description: Draws the string in the current graphics context using the specified bounding rectangle, font and attributes.

InstanceMethods.Name: drawWithRect:options:attributes:
InstanceMethods.Description: Draws the receiver with the specified options and other display characteristics of the given attributes, within the specified rectangle in the current graphics context.

InstanceMethods.Name: boundingRectWithSize:options:attributes:
InstanceMethods.Description: Calculates and returns the bounding rect for the receiver drawn using the given options and display characteristics, within the specified rectangle in the current graphics context.

InstanceProperties.Description: This NSString object.

TypeMethods.Name: stringWithFormat:

TypeMethods.Name: localizedStringWithFormat:
TypeMethods.Description: Returns a string created by using a given format string as a template into which the remaining argument values are substituted according to the current locale.

TypeMethods.Name: localizedUserNotificationStringForKey:arguments:
